verses.roman:
keha jala āni' deya mahāprabhura kare
keha jala deya tāṅra caraṇa-upare

synonyms: keha—someone; jala āni'—bringing water; deya—delivers; mahāprabhura kare—to the hand of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; keha—someone; jala deya—pours water; tāṅra—His; caraṇa-upare—on the lotus feet.
translation: Someone brought water to pour into the hands of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu, and someone poured water on His lotus feet.
